# start Validation Reply Form
_vrf_PLAT112_jin19               
;
PROBLEM: ADDSYM Detects New (Pseudo) Symm. Elem.      b/2         90 %Fit  
RESPONSE: The pseudo-symmetry in not crystallographic symmetry
and the b axis length is indeed as reported. 
;
_vrf_PLAT303_jin19               
;
PROBLEM: Full Occupancy H-Atom  H3A    with # Connections       1.15 Check 
RESPONSE: Atom H3a seems to form a strong hydrogen bond with a
partially occupied atom Br3a (15% occupancy) and the program interprets 
the short bond (1.940 Ang) as a possible reason for H-atom disorder. 
The current model is computationally stable.
;
_vrf_PLAT342_jin19               
;
PROBLEM: Low Bond Precision on  C-C Bonds ...............    0.01378 Ang.  
RESPONSE: This stems from the pseudo-symmetry is disorder of the Pb atoms.
;
_vrf_PLAT906_jin19               
;
PROBLEM: Large K value in the Analysis of Variance ......      5.077 Check 
RESPONSE: This stems from the pseudo-symmetry is disorder of the Pb atoms.
;
_vrf_PLAT911_jin19               
;
PROBLEM: Missing # FCF Refl Between THmin & STh/L=  0.595         13 Report
RESPONSE: 
We believe that there is a good reason to use statistical analysis and 
if some reflections are outliers they harm rather than improve the 
refinement.  The statistical analysis was conducted with program 
G4_fcf_filter published on my web site 
http://xray.chem.wisc.edu/Resources.html. 
 It uses the approach described by Prince, E., Nicholson, W.L. 
(1983) Acta Cryst A39, 407-410. For the suggested value for the 
outlier cutoff see Rollett J.S. (1988) Crystallographic Computing 
4, 149-166, Oxford University Press.
;
_vrf_PLAT971_jin19               
;
PROBLEM: Check Calcd Residual Density  0.82A From    Pb2A       1.85 eA-3  
RESPONSE: This peaks is in the vicinity of a heavy element and
is considered noise.
;
_vrf_PLAT977_jin19               
;
PROBLEM: Check the Negative Difference Density on    H1AA      -0.34 eA-3  
RESPONSE: This stems from the pseudo-symmetry is disorder of the Pb atoms.
;
_vrf_PLAT978_jin19               
;
PROBLEM: Number C-C Bonds with Positive Residual Density           0 Note  
RESPONSE: This message does not indicate the structure is deficient. 
With the disorder and pseudo-symmetry it is hard to expect an 
ideal behavior.
;
# end Validation Reply Form
